==English==

===Noun===
'''exaction'''

# The act of [[demand]]ing with [[authority]], and [[compel]]ling to [[pay]] or [[yield]]; [[compulsion]] to give or [[furnish]]; a [[levy]]ing by [[force]]; a driving to [[compliance]]; as, the exaction to tribute or of obedience; hence, [[extortion]].
# That which is [[exact]]ed; a severe [[tribute]]; a [[fee]], [[reward]], or [[contribution]], demanded or levied with [[severity]] or [[injustice]].

